                            <comment id="17625339" author="risdenk" created="Thu, 27 Oct 2022 21:20:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is still happening. I ran into this after smoke testing Solr 9.1 RC:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
risdenk          11794   0.0  0.0 408638832   1392   ??  S    10:13AM   0:00.01 scdaemon --multi-server --homedir /tmp/smoke_solr_9.1.0_eadc4178b30af782a21cb739122a1bafbc6ae99b/solr.gpg
risdenk          11793   0.0  0.0 408712032   1376   ??  Ss   10:13AM   0:01.32 gpg-agent --homedir /tmp/smoke_solr_9.1.0_eadc4178b30af782a21cb739122a1bafbc6ae99b/solr.gpg --use-standard-socket --daemon
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17625340" author="risdenk" created="Thu, 27 Oct 2022 21:25:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=houston&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;houston&quot;&gt;houston&lt;/a&gt; not sure this is in the area that GPG stuff was changed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17625344" author="houston" created="Thu, 27 Oct 2022 21:48:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t touched the GPG in the smoke tester, just for the steps that the release manager takes. Can look into this tomorrow though&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17632469" author="risdenk" created="Fri, 11 Nov 2022 16:54:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like this will do it:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
gpgconf --homedir /tmp/smoke_solr_9.1.0_aa4f3d98ab19c201e7f3c74cd14c99174148616d/solr.gpg --kill gpg-agent
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where homedir is `gpgHomeDir`&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17632470" author="houston" created="Fri, 11 Nov 2022 16:56:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;But what command in the smoketester is causing the leaked agents? I couldn&apos;t find anything&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17632474" author="risdenk" created="Fri, 11 Nov 2022 17:12:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;any gpg command can start the gpg-agent. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you have `use-agent` in ~/.gnupg/gpg.conf or maybe its the default not 100% sure. There used to be an option &quot;--no-use-agent&quot; but that isn&apos;t valid anymore after some GPG version. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From what I&apos;ve checked - it doesn&apos;t matter if it tries to kill an agent that doesn&apos;t exist.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17632475" author="risdenk" created="Fri, 11 Nov 2022 17:13:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you have --homedir set - then gpg agent spins up a second one instead of using the default one that looks at `~/.gnupg` so thats how we end up with multiple gpg agents since each smoke test run is separate homedir. If homedir wasn&apos;t set the default agent would be used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
